76561198047460236,Recommended,220660,8641864,"Posted: 9 January, 2014",all,Orion_Prime,"its a decent game, but not everyone will enjoy it.Some parts of it could use more works from devs, but that's not gonna happen - they moved on to making next game which will have some parts similar to Stardrive.What i liked a lot:1.Ship design - very good, complex ship design. How you place stuff (armor, power, weapons, etc) really matters. Also very fun to do.2. Combat - nice looking, dynamic combat.What is not so good (can be fixed by good mods though):1. Tech tree could be better.2. The game has a very strong snowballing effect - each civ's development is exponential and so minor differences in how you/computer micromanges stuff can lead to massive difference between civs' development/power in mid and late game. Can go both ways - you or one of AI opponents will become massively owerpowered compared to rest of universe at which point it will be much less fun.Also no multiplayer and there will not be any.Would i recommend this game? - Maybe.If you, like me, like detailed and complex ship design and lots of micro of both economy and combat in such single player games - then you will get a good number of hours of fun from this game even without mods. If so get it especially if its on sale.For comparison, I like this game more then Galactic Civ II and Space Empires V, almost exclusively because of massively better and more fun combat and ship design system."
