76561198005923854,Not Recommended,220660,17275529,"Posted: 28 July, 2015",all,Yulgalminakf,"Edit: Having played the game for more than a couple of hours, I see the game falling apart in my hands. Glitches, crashes, saves corrupting, it all sucks. The basic gameplay is fun, but the game is unfinished, as-in prelaunch. It's a beta, not a finished product. The developers have completely moved onto a sequel instead of finished the game they already produced, and the reviews I'm hearing for that game sound exactly like this review. User content patches do what they can, but they can't finish the game for the producers.The overall gameplay is fun, if you can get past the awkward GUI.Ship building is complicated and fun. Building and conquering is well balanced. I just can't get past the GUI.Frankly, the GUI in this game is terrible, it's my number one complaint of this whole game. This is strange coming from the developers of Endless Space which has a perfect, smooth, awesome GUI.What's wrong with the GUI you ask? Several things.-Clicking on a button doesn't ""always"" click it. It just doesn't respond... it just.... doesn't....-Opening and closing the windows is awkward. The close button changes locations on every screen and disappears completely on others.-They tried to integrate some UI stuff from Endless Space, such as right clicking a window to make it close. However, it's not availble on every screen, so it just takes some testing and memorizing to find out which screen closes with right click which screen doesn't.-Information on several screens is just a mess, while on others it's just a massive block of text. Nothing seems to be organized very well or effeciently.-Ship selection is the biggest complaint I have of the GUI.-You can make control groups just fine, but shift + # doesn't add the current selection to the #'d control group. Having the control group you want to add to selected and shift+click-drag doesn't help either because that selects non-military ships as well.-You can't unselect a ship from the selection panel in the bottom left corner.-Ships move at different speeds, but there's no way to make a fleet/control group to move at the speed of the slowest ship.Overall, it just feels strange to navigate the UI. Some may call this nit-picking, but I don't. A game like this needs a smooth and fluid UI to be able to manage everything easily and quickly, while getting all the information you need on the fly. This game does not deliver on that.Another con of this game is the sound design. When ships are fighting, most of the time, you don't hear anything at all. Sometimes you hear the ship firing, and you get a 1/100 chance for the sound of the weapons firing to BLOW OUT your speakers. Turning the volume down doesn't help because then you can't hear any of the other sounds in the game. So, inevitablly, you just end up turning off the sound completely to avoid the jump scare every few minutes.After muddling through this game's crummy GUI, getting my ears checked by my doctor, and reloading the game through the crashes and the MASSIVE glitches, I'd give this game a D. Would not recommend this headache."
