76561198009042866,Recommended,220660,14931715,"Posted: 17 March, 2015",all,thearson53,"Well, I saw a lot of varying reviews, but the game was on sale and I gave it a shot. I've probably put in around 20-30 hours now, and I must say I find this game really addicting. The user interface takes a little time to get used to, but once you get the hang of it, the game's dynamics are pretty fun. The game is technically turn based in a sense, but turns are measured by time (every 5 seconds) which you can alter during gameplay, or even pause to get your orders out first, so the game is actually played as if all in realtime. In ship combat, you basically just tell your ships to attack the bad guys, so if you like to manuever fleets and such this game may not be for you. You manage just about everything for your species, which is pretty neat. And of course, you design your ships if you want. It may be time consuming, but is pretty fun. You choose a hull type, and then you are responsible for setting up the rest. Also, when you create a new ship, don't name it the same as ships you already have in play, because then you won't be able to refit your current ships. All in all, I would give this game an 8.5 out of 10. It is fun, and as you keep progressing, you can't help but to want to stick around and see what comes next. The graphics are fine, nothing super spectacular, but are still decent enough. I wouldn't pay 30 bucks for the game, but for 10, absolutely."
