76561198004695068,Recommended,220660,8506896,"Posted: 2 January, 2014",all,Evil_Jinius,"This is quite a nice game. The lack of a nicely paced tutorial and some of the controls being not so intuitive (but once you learnt it, either by google or the game's wiki, it's not a problem no more) might put off some, but in my opinion, this game is a gem.A typical 4X turn-based game can more often than not turn into a flutter of clicks while you wait, or at times, there's just so much info and decisions to go through, that sometimes each turn can take a whole lot of time. The ""real-time"" concept in this game is a good balance. You can speed up, slow down and pause, in other words, you dictate the pacing of the game.Space battles are cool and there's quite a bit of getting used to here... meaning to say, there's some interesting tactics... like making your ships charge and come around at slower ships... allows a more maneuverable but less powerful ship to bring down a slower brute... or a swarm of light ships can do more damage to one or a few powerful capital class ships...Of course, there are things to be improved... research can be painstakingly slow, but perhaps it's because there are not that many things to research... or that it's one way to stretch the game, I don't know. I would be happy to have some mods or DLCs with new techs...I'd say, if you liked MOO 1 and 2... and after getting Sins of a Solar empire, and you feel you want something in between of these games... Definitely go for StarDrive...Cheers!"
