,Recommended,220660,8301815,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,Sir Scarfalot,"This game is AWESOME. It really recaptures the whole vibe from my favorite game of all time, Master of Orion 2. Alas, it does not quite reach that height, but it certainly comes CLOSE. Closer perhaps than any other game of its type or genre. I just love building ships, designing how they work, what they use, the tactical considerations and concessions to various limitations.A lot of reviews criticize its lack of polish, but it is improving. There are community mods and expansions that extend the game considerably (I personally only use the Station Symmetry mod, the lopsided vanilla stations aggravate my OCD). I would say that it should have remained in ""beta"" for longer, but it it is still very fun to play.I would argue that it is actually a very stable game. There are scattered issues with the savegame, but nothing game-breaking. If you're having problems, don't forget to do the old ""Verify integrity of game cache"" option; I haven't seen that fail yet."
