76561198063970359,Recommended,220660,8966225,"Posted: 3 February, 2014",all,ImAHungryMan,approved
,Recommended,220660,8541619,"Posted: 3 January, 2014",all,weregamer,"I'm somewhat on the fence about this game, but I think I can say I recommend it with reservations.The real-time approach is often a mistake in making a 4X game; StarDrive manages to avoid most of the big problems that other recent attempts (most notably the terribly disappointing Armada 2526) have had. The mechanics make sense, and the player can make informed choices to wring out advantages to actually win battles, wars, and the game. Custom ship designs are a key part of the value proposition of the game, and the implementation here is meaty and satisfying.Those good things said, the game has some big flaws in usability/playability. There is often only one way to perform an action  (scrap/refit a ship, scroll the map) when there should be several; information displays like the known-planets list and ships list are missing key features. Also, while the ship design module is a lot of fun early in the tech tree, as ships get larger the lack of any automated support makes filling in all the boxes of a design tedious instead of fun.I picked StarDrive up as part of the holiday sale, and I can say it was worth the discounted price to me, but I'm not sure it would be worth full price."
