76561198044268103,Not Recommended,220660,23565663,"Posted: 15 June, 2016",all,SphereBeaker,"I really wanted to like StarDrive.  It reminded me of the old Stars! game for Windows 3.1, where you would define your alien race, expand, conquere, research and design new ship layouts.  It sounded like a great modern update.  But after playing for a while, expanding a lot, and making a large fleet, I tried to attack a small faction and lost for no good reason.  It feels like there's a ""correct"" way to play this game and they never tell you anything about how to play it.  For instance, to conquer a planet, you have to take out the ships guarding it, and then send colonists over in separate transport ships to fight on the ground, which is heavily favoured to the defender.  You have to outnumber them like 10-1 to have a hope of taking the place.  So after spending an untold effort in trying to take ONE planet from a small faction, my faction gets into a civil war and my homeworld gets heavily attacked, at which point I lost all interest in this game.The mechanics are clunky and not at all expained.  To top it off, it seem like a lot of features where left unfinished in favour of working on the sequel, so overall, I would say avoid.  I mean really, 75% of the 4x games on steam are space based like this.  Search games by tag and find a good one to play."
