76561198047169453,Not Recommended,220660,22682583,"Posted: 27 April, 2016",all,DeinonychusCowboy,"I really would LIKE to like this game. My favorite part about it is the races - they're very cool and very well designed, and have some great animated assets, and I love the take on race customization the game uses.Unfortunately, however, this game seems to have been thrown together in the 4X space formula without any polish, refinement, or novel central ideas, and the gameplay suffers terribly because of it. I literally cannot get through a full game in StarDrive. Everything is quirky, unbalanced, hard to find, and unpredictable. Even more of a shame considering the ship designer is one of the less obtuse examples I've seen in games like this. With a UI redesign and a lot of balancing and mechanical refinement, this could be a really cool game. But it's not, and the devs have abandoned it, so don't be fooled by the cool races and graphics."
